  },
  "payload": {
    "gradient": {
      "initial": [
        { "name": "Initial Denaturation", "temperature": 95, "duration": "1-2 min" }
      ],
      "cycles": [
        {
          "repeats": 30,
          "steps": [
            { "name": "Denaturation", "temperature": 95, "duration": "45 sec" },
            { "name": "Annealing", "temperature": 55, "duration": "30 sec" },
            { "name": "Extension", "temperature": 72, "duration": "2 min/kb" }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "final": [
        { "name": "Final Extension", "temperature": 72, "duration": "5 min" }
      ],
      "hold": { "name": "Hold", "temperature": 4, "duration": "Indef." }
    },
    "ingredients": [
      { "id": "1", "name": "Pfu 10X Reaction Buffer with MgSO4", "concentration": "10X (1X final, 2 mM Mg2+)", "amount_per_reaction": "5" },
      { "id": "2", "name": "dNTP Mix", "concentration": "10 mM (200 uM each final)", "amount_per_reaction": "1" },
      { "id": "3", "name": "Forward Primer", "concentration": "10 uM (0.5 uM final)", "amount_per_reaction": "2.5" },
      { "id": "4", "name": "Reverse Primer", "concentration": "10 uM (0.5 uM final)", "amount_per_reaction": "2.5" },
      { "id": "5", "name": "Template DNA", "concentration": "< 0.5 ug", "amount_per_reaction": "variable" },
      { "id": "6", "name": "Pfu DNA Polymerase", "concentration": "2-3 U/uL (1.25 U/50 uL final)", "amount_per_reaction": "0.5" },
      { "id": "7", "name": "Nuclease-free Water", "concentration": "-", "amount_per_reaction": "to 50" }
    ],
    "notes": "Vendor: Promega, Pfu DNA Polymerase (Cat. M7741). Add Pfu LAST, after the dNTPs (its 3'->5' exonuclease degrades primers otherwise). Pfu extends slowly: ~2 min/kb at 72 C (minimum 1 min). Do not exceed 2 min at 95 C for the initial denaturation. Annealing 42-65 C depending on the primers; raise it for high-Tm primers to cut primer-dimer. The 55 C shown is a placeholder starting point. Primers 0.1-1.0 uM (5-50 pmol). Cycles 25-35. 1X buffer = 2 mM Mg2+ (as MgSO4). Preheat the cycler to 95 C before loading. Source: https://www.promega.com/-/media/files/resources/protocols/product-information-sheets/g/pfu-dna-polymerase-protocol.pdf"
  }
